        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Border Patrol Pay Parity Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill increases pay rates for U.S. Border Patrol agents.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The bill specifies that the Office of Personnel Management (OPM) must increase the minimum rate of pay for GS-12 Border Patrol agents by at least 14%. It also directs OPM to increase pay rates for other grades, levels, occupational groups, or similar classifications as specified by the Department of Homeland Security.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The increases must be made on or before January 1, 2024.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;!--tinycomments|2.1|data:application/json;base64,--&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
